cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI. 

This paper is about named entity recognition from code-switching Twitter data, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a model that uses transfer learning and token replacement to address out-of-vocabulary words, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of hierarchical architecture and normalization techniques can be categorized under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also uses bilingual character representation, which is a technique commonly used in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for natural language processing tasks. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of data noise, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
